And they joined the armies blue.</ref><note xml:id="ref_21150">THE SLAVES ... ARMIES BLUE [Allusion historical] According to (The War of the Rebellion: A Compilation of the Official Records of the Union and Confederate Armies), around 19,000 slaves abandoned plantations to join Sherman’s march (qtd in Edmund Drago’s “How Sherman’s March Through Georgia Affected the Slaves,” The Georgia Historical Quarterly, 363).
(Leslie McAbee)</note>
